2 0 obj
<< /Length 1543 >>
stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 785 Td
14 TL
() Tj
T*
(A1886 GEP DATASET CHECKER ALGORITHM SUMMARY V01) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026.06.24) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This note summarizes the red-line processing used in the browser viewer:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  1. Deglitch function) Tj
T*
(  2. Optional rule01 range-threshold function) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The blue line is the raw r0 data. The red line is the displayed processed range after) Tj
T*
(deglitching and, when enabled, rule01.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Deglitch Function) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Purpose: remove short abnormal spikes while preserving normal range movement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Inputs:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - r0[k]: raw range value at frame k) Tj
T*
(  - median_win: local median window size, default 9) Tj
T*
(  - spike_TH: spike threshold in meters, default 0.065 m) Tj
T*
(  - jump_TH: jump threshold in meters, default 0.253 m) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For each frame k:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  1. Build a local window around r0[k].) Tj
T*
(  2. Compute the local median value.) Tj
T*
(  3. Compare the current raw value with the local median.) Tj
T*
(  4. Compare the current raw value with the previous accepted value.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pseudocode:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(prev_valid = r0[0]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(for each k:) Tj
T*
(    x = r0[k]) Tj
T*
(    med = median\(local window around k\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    spike_flag = abs\(x - med\) > spike_TH) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    jump_flag =) Tj
T*
(        abs\(x - prev_valid\) > jump_TH) Tj
T*
(        and abs\(med - prev_valid\) <= spike_TH) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Page 1 of 3) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
3 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 8 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 1 0 R >> >> /Contents 2 0 R >>
endobj
4 0 obj
<< /Length 1531 >>
stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 785 Td
14 TL
(    if spike_flag or jump_flag:) Tj
T*
(        y = med) Tj
T*
(    else:) Tj
T*
(        y = x) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    red_base[k] = y) Tj
T*
(    prev_valid = y) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Brief explanation:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - spike_flag catches one-point or short noisy spikes far from the local trend.) Tj
T*
(  - jump_flag catches sudden jumps away from the previous trusted value when the local) Tj
T*
(  median still agrees with the previous trusted value.) Tj
T*
(  - The replacement value is the local median, so the red curve follows the nearby) Tj
T*
(  stable trend instead of the spike.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Optional Rule01 Function) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Purpose: block processed values that jump into an untrusted high-range region.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Inputs:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - red_base[k]: result from the deglitch function) Tj
T*
(  - rule_base_range_TH: untrusted range threshold, default 1.1 m) Tj
T*
(  - Enable rule01: checkbox that turns this rule on or off) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Rule:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(old_r0 = r0{k}) Tj
T*
(new_r0 = r0{k+1}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(if new_r0 >= rule_base_range_TH:) Tj
T*
(    r0{k+1} = r0{k}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Viewer behavior:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - Rule01 is applied after the deglitch function.) Tj
T*
(  - The final red curve uses the rule01-corrected values.) Tj
T*
(  - Any point changed by rule01 is marked with a green dot.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pseudocode:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(red_final = copy\(red_base\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(if Enable rule01:) Tj
T*
(Page 2 of 3) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
